      RugSeekers
   =20
 =20
Here  is a story about =E2=80=9Ca 52-year-old grandfather in a Dogecoin hat=
 [who] is patrolling the darkest corners of the crypto world for Shit Coin =
scammers=E2=80=9D:Robert Browning and his motley crew =E2=80=94 named the R=
ugSeekers for a popular pump and dump scam called the rug pull =E2=80=94 ar=
e investigating a tip about a new coin called We Save Moon. They=E2=80=99re=
 examining its source code, wallets and price charts for red flags indicati=
ng fraud. Browning enters the coin=E2=80=99s group chat on Telegram, the me=
ssaging app where this world hangs out. He starts typing under his alias Ro=
bAte25 =E2=80=94 a reference to his grandson=E2=80=99s birthday, 8/25 =E2=
=80=94 and moves in for the kill.Here=E2=80=99s how the chat starts:RobAte2=
5: Are there any modsWe Save Moon: we are here for you as alwaysRobAte25: H=
elloWe Save Moon: let=E2=80=99s PUMP and get this party startWell that seem=
s like the kill, no?=C2=A0And yet it goes on for a long time from there. He=
 asks questions about the identity of the developers. =E2=80=9CWhat=E2=80=
=99s the utility of the coin,=E2=80=9D asks another RugSeeker. (The answer =
is that =E2=80=9Cpeople get all kind of rewards.=E2=80=9D) The RugSeekers d=
o test transactions to see how the liquidity pool operates. (Trickily.) Eve=
ryone pretends that this is very serious difficult high-tech stuff.Did you =
read the start of the chat that I quoted? =E2=80=9CLet's PUMP and get this =
party start,=E2=80=9D say the developers of We Save Moon, immediately, to a=
 stranger on the internet, in reply to his penetrating investigative questi=
on =E2=80=9CHello.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0I know all I need to know about whether We=
 Save Moon is a scam! But RugSeekers keep seeking.=C2=A0In crypto, =E2=80=
=9Cwe=E2=80=99re going to pump a worthless thing to make money for ourselve=
s=E2=80=9D is just=C2=A0normal stuff; people=C2=A0want=C2=A0to invest in pu=
mps. Just not the bad ones.=C2=A0
