      Things happen
   =20
 =20
Moderna=E2=80=99s Concerns About  Omicron Outlook Spark Market Slump. The i=
nside story of the Pfizer vaccine: =E2=80=98a once-in-an-epoch windfall.=E2=
=80=99 Goldman Sachs Rolls Out New Worker Benefits to Combat Employee Burno=
ut. Facebook Owner Meta Must  Sell Giphy on Competition Concerns, U.K. Says=
.=C2=A0Hertz Targets $2 Billion in Buybacks Amid Pandemic Recovery. Activis=
t calls on Glencore to spin off coal assets.=C2=A0Expert Networks Aren=E2=
=80=99t Just for Hedge Funds Anymore. Microsoft=E2=80=99s Satya Nadella Sel=
ls Half of His Shares in the Company. Twitter=E2=80=99s Agrawal Is  Younges=
t CEO in S&P 500, Nudging Out Zuckerberg.=C2=A0When Shipping Containers Are=
 Abandoned, the Cargo Becomes a  Mystery Prize. Learning Sixteenth-Century =
Business Jargon.=C2=A0What is Waystar Royco=E2=80=99s true valuation? Mergi=
ng black holes may create bubbles that could swallow the universe.If you'd =
like to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, right in your i=
nbox, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe to Money Stu=
ff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] I suppose technic=
ally it=E2=80=99s a letter, but in practical English-language usage it=E2=
=80=99s a word.[2] Also if it was scarce people wouldn=E2=80=99t use it! Pu=
blic-health agencies don=E2=80=99t go around naming coronavirus variants, l=
ike, =E2=80=9Cthe Super Bowl variant,=E2=80=9D because then they=E2=80=99d =
get sued=C2=A0and have to pay the intellectual-property-rights owners.[3] D=
own here in the footnotes you and I can talk like rational people and say: =
Look, if it=E2=80=99s essentially free to create these scarce claims, can=
=E2=80=99t anyone just create more of them, defeating the promise of scarci=
ty? Can=E2=80=99t I go launch a thing and call it Omicron Coin and sell it =
to compete with the existing Omicron Coin? Can=E2=80=99t anybody do that? S=
houldn=E2=80=99t there be hundreds of Omicron Coin projects all competing f=
or the money looking to speculate on the word =E2=80=9Comicron=E2=80=9D? Su=
re, man, I dunno. I should say that the limits here seem to be more social =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0about what projects get attention on what crypto websites an=
d chats, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0rather than technical, and our rational object=
ions probably don=E2=80=99t carry much weight. In the early days of Bitcoin=
, Bitcoin proponents said =E2=80=9Conly 21 million Bitcoins will ever be mi=
nted so they will go up in value,=E2=80=9D and Bitcoin skeptics said =E2=80=
=9Cno, if they become valuable, then people can just create new Bitcoin cop=
ycats and siphon away that value.=E2=80=9D The skeptics were not *entirely*=
 wrong =E2=80=94=C2=A0there are copycats=C2=A0like Dogecoin that really did=
 become valuable =E2=80=94=C2=A0but they were *almost* entirely wrong; a Bi=
tcoin clone did not turn out to be a good substitute for Bitcoin.[4] See pa=
ge 57 here: =E2=80=9CIn connection with the offering of these notes in 2014=
, we purchased a convertible note hedges for $603.4 million and sold warran=
ts [for] $389.2 million.=E2=80=9D[5] This is a rough number and requires so=
me explanation. The $214 million net premium number is actually for two dif=
ferent call spreads, relating to Tesla=E2=80=99s convertibles maturing in 2=
019 and 2021. The 2019 convertible matured out of the money (see page 22 he=
re) and so Tesla=E2=80=99s call-spread premium was effectively wasted. The =
2021 convertible matured ridiculously in-the-money and everyone converted (=
see page 20 here). The actual result involved net share settlement of the b=
onds, bond hedge and warrants, but the basic *economic* result is that (1) =
Tesla bought a call spread on the 3.8 million shares of stock underlying th=
e 2021 convertible, (2) that call spread had strikes of $359.87 and $560.63=
88, a difference of about $200.77 per share, and (3) both legs ended up in =
the money. So Tesla got back value equal to about the $200.77 width of the =
call spread times the 3.8 million underlying shares, or about $760 million.=
 (The share and per-share numbers are as of 2014, when the trades were done=
; since then Tesla had a stock split, which changes the share numbers but n=
ot the total value.) This is probably not quite right due to differences in=
 timing of settlement, etc., but it=E2=80=99s in the right ballpark.[6] Dis=
closure, I used to do these trades as a banker. =E2=80=9CYou buy a call spr=
ead from us and the IRS will pay for it=E2=80=9D: Definitely a thing I said=
!
